cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper describes a machine learning approach for generating patient-specific organ motion models from medical images, using generative neural networks conditioned on the input image. This falls under the broad category of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG), with specific applications in medical imaging and biomechanics. The paper also involves the use of discriminative neural networks (cs.AI) and optimisation techniques (cs.NE) for training the generative models. Finally, the paper evaluates the accuracy of the generated motion models (cs.MM).
